article.headline: Hampton 81, Morgan State 48
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Lionel Pehoua had 15 points and nine rebounds to lead Hampton to an 81-48 win over Morgan State on Saturday night. The Pirates (11-9, 9-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) led 37-8 at the half. The Bears (2-20, 2-9) shot 6.5 percent from the floor in the first half, scoring only eight points, half of them from the free throw line. Morgan State turned it on in the second half, scoring 40 points to Hampton's 44, but was haunted by its first half mistakes to shoot 23 percent for the night. The Pirates shot 51.9 percent from the field. Hampton outrebounded the Bears 57-34. Joseph McLean led Morgan State with 13 points and 10 rebounds. No other player scored in double digits for the Bears. Demario Mattox added 13 points for Hampton.
